{In the sixth chapter, we'll cover 3...c5 & 3...Be7!?, one of the last sidelines against the 3.Bg5 system.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Bg5 c5 {trying to undermine our center.} (3... Be7 4. Nc3 b6 {Black delays playing ...d5/c5. However, this runs into a thematic plan.} (4... d5 {transposes to the QGD lines.}) (4... O-O {allows White to expand in the center with} 5. e4 $14 {[%csl Gc4,Gd4,Ge4] White keeps a massive center.}) (4... h6 5. Bh4 d5 {tr.}) 5. e4 {[%csl Gc4,Gd4,Ge4] we build a massive center.} Bb7 (5... Nxe4 {doesn't work. After} 6. Bxe7 Nxc3 7. Bxd8 Nxd1 8. Bxc7 Nxb2 9. Rb1 Na4 10. Bd3 $16 {the combo of bishop pair +pawn structure is quite strong. The knight on a4 is also offside.}) 6. Qc2 c5 $5 {the only challenging response. They try to undermine our center. After the usual} (6... d6 7. O-O-O $16) 7. Bxf6 Bxf6 8. e5 cxd4 (8... Be7 9. d5 $16 {[%csl Gc4,Gd5,Ge5]}) 9. exf6 dxc3 10. fxg7 Rg8 11. Qxh7 $14 {[%cal Gb2b3,Gg1e2,Ge2c3] White remains somewhat better.}) 4. d5 exd5 5. cxd5 d6 {delaying ...h6 intentionally. This favours White.} 6. e4 h6 {here, instead of playing the usual Bh4, we can play the rather strong} (6... Be7 7. Bf4 $1 {Black cannot play ...Nxe4 here due to Qa4+!} O-O 8. Nc3 Re8 9. Bd3 Bf8 10. Nge2 $14 {[%csl Gc3,Gd3,Ge2,Gf4] we end up stabilising the center and keep a small edge due to our lead in development and somewhat extra space.}) 7. Be3 $1 $14 {[%csl Ge4][%cal Gd1a4,Ga4e4] defending e4 tactically.} g6 (7... Be7 8. Nc3 Nbd7 9. h3 $16 {[%csl Gd5,Ge4] White keeps the usual space advantage.}) (7... Qe7 $5 {this doesn't win a pawn. After} 8. Nc3 a6 9. Bd3 {we have stabilised.} Nbd7 (9... b5 $6 {too hasty.} 10. h3 $1 {we are in no rush. We prepare Nf3.} Nbd7 11. Nf3 g5 (11... g6 12. O-O Bg7 13. Qd2 $16 {they have problems with castling.}) 12. O-O Bg7 13. b4 {[%cal Rc5c4,Gf3d4,Gd4f5,Gd3c2] striking at the right time! There's too many weaknesses in Black's camp.}) 10. h3 {covering the g4-square to prepare Nf3.} (10. Nf3 Ng4 $132) 10... Ne5 11. Nf3 Nfd7 12. Nxe5 Nxe5 13. f4 Qh4+ 14. Ke2 Nxd3 15. Qxd3 $14 {White ends up keeping a huge spatial advantage. Our king remains quite safe.}) 8. Nc3 Bg7 9. h3 O-O 10. Nf3 {we play for the thematic spatial advantage.} b5 {This is considered to be the best liquidation attempt for Black. However, after} (10... Re8 11. Nd2 $14 {[%csl Gc3,Gd2,Gd4,Gd5,Ge4][%cal Gf1e2,Ra7a6,Ra2a4] White has wonderfully stabilised the center. ...a6 will be met with a4.}) (10... a6 11. a4 Re8 12. Nd2 $14) 11. e5 dxe5 12. Bxb5 $1 e4 13. Ne5 Nh5 14. Nc4 $14 {[%csl Gd5] White remains better. We have a passed pawn, better pawn structure and more active pieces in the center.} *

